modules.description: Handles incoming HTTP/2 connections on a stream socket. It initializes a connection with a provided configuration, directs each incoming request to a specified handler, and routes errors to an error-handling function. This module is used to build HTTP/2 servers that process requests over secure or plaintext TCP streams.

This module implements HTTP/2 client functionality over Eio, managing connections and requests. It provides operations to create connections, send requests with response handlers, and manage connection lifecycle with ping, shutdown, and close-checking operations. Concrete use cases include sending HTTP/2 requests over TLS or TCP streams and handling server push and trailers.

This module provides HTTP/2 communication capabilities over Eio, supporting both server and client implementations. It enables handling incoming requests with custom logic, sending requests with support for streaming responses, and managing connection lifecycles with operations like ping, shutdown, and close detection. The module supports secure and plaintext transports, and handles advanced HTTP/2 features like server push and trailers. Example uses include building HTTP/2 servers that process requests over TLS and writing clients that send concurrent requests with streaming response handling.
